We're putting you on what we call
"sudden death academic probation".

06:02.436 --> 06:04.437
And what does that entail?

06:04.605 --> 06:06.897
It entails that if you
fail another class,

06:07.064 --> 06:09.315
you'll be asked
to leave Rushmore.

06:09.482 --> 06:11.151
In other words,
I'll be expelled.

06:11.275 --> 06:12.568
That's correct.

06:12.694 --> 06:15.322
Could I see some documentation
on that, please?

06:16.907 --> 06:19.117
Too many extracurricular
activities, Max.

06:19.243 --> 06:21.371
Not enough studying.

06:25.332 --> 06:28.876
Dr. Guggenheim, I don't want
to tell you how to do your job,

06:28.960 --> 06:30.919
but, the fact is,
no matter how hard I try,

06:31.002 --> 06:33.004
I still might
flunk another class.

06:33.129 --> 06:36.927
If that means I have to stay on for a
postgraduate year, then so be it, but...

06:37.010 --> 06:39.096
We don't offer
a postgraduate year.

06:39.221 --> 06:42.223
Well... we don't offer it yet.

06:42.306 --> 06:44.308
Just bring up the grades.

06:45.142 --> 06:48.146
Do you remember how
I got into this school?

06:48.313 --> 06:52.315
- Yes. You wrote a play.
- That's right.

06:52.399 --> 06:56.530
Second grade.
A little one act about Watergate.

06:56.613 --> 06:59.032
And my mother read it
and felt I should go to Rushmore.

06:59.116 --> 07:02.201
And you read it, and
you gave me a scholarship, didn't you?

07:02.827 --> 07:04.370
Mm-hmm.

07:04.453 --> 07:07.414
- Do you regret it?
- No, I don't regret it.

07:07.581 --> 07:10.125
But I still might
have to expel you.

07:10.333 --> 07:12.086
Couldn't...

07:12.169 --> 07:14.838
Couldn't we just
let me float by?

07:15.465 --> 07:17.090
For old time's sake?

07:17.257 --> 07:19.301
Can't do it, Max.

07:20.720 --> 07:23.763
- They want to kick me out.
- Oh, no, not again.

07:23.889 --> 07:26.433
- What are you gonna do?
- The only thing I can do:

07:26.557 --> 07:29.021
try and pull some strings
with the administration, I guess.

07:34.233 --> 07:36.443
Did you hear they're teaching
Japanese next year?

07:36.567 --> 07:38.527
That's the rumor.

07:38.944 --> 07:40.655
And they're canceling Latin.

07:40.822 --> 07:42.366
What?

07:42.533 --> 07:45.452
I tried to get Latin
canceled for five years.

07:45.577 --> 07:47.621
"It's a dead language,"
I'd always say.

07:47.747 --> 07:50.750
Well, I guess
they finally heard you.

08:05.971 --> 08:07.222
Excuse me.

08:08.263 --> 08:09.975
Could I please see a list
of all the people...

08:10.059 --> 08:12.185
