The Lad with the Silver Button. "

09:14.286 --> 09:16.579
- Meet me on the corner in ten minutes.
- Where are you going?

09:16.662 --> 09:18.710
I'll tell you
in the squad car.

09:18.876 --> 09:20.753
Oh, and, Willie,

09:20.879 --> 09:23.130
you were wrong
about Enrique Sanchez.

09:23.255 --> 09:25.591
He died in his sleep.

09:26.216 --> 09:28.174
Excellent. That was excellent.

09:28.301 --> 09:30.176
That was great.
That was great.

09:30.218 --> 09:33.764
Um, Irving... could you get some
root beers for anybody who wants one?

09:33.890 --> 09:35.559
- I don't want one, okay?
- Okay.

09:35.726 --> 09:37.603
All right, next scene.

09:38.477 --> 09:41.856
Frank, you enter stage right
with a bag of cocaine.

09:42.024 --> 09:44.650
I was just telling Mr. Calloway
the other day how fortunate we are...

09:44.734 --> 09:46.255
- to have someone like
you looking out for Dirk.

09:46.256 --> 09:47.777
Oh, don't be silly.

09:47.944 --> 09:50.363
Dirk's a great kid,
and I'm just trying to impart...

09:50.488 --> 09:54.619
some of the experiences
I've accrued to help him.

09:54.744 --> 09:56.911
This has my number on it
if you need to call me...

09:57.036 --> 10:00.040
or need help with Dirk
or anything like that.

10:00.165 --> 10:02.667
Well, thank you very much.
Hello, Dirk.

10:02.751 --> 10:04.837
- Hi, Mom.
- How are you, honey?

10:04.962 --> 10:06.629
- Fine.
- Bye.

10:06.754 --> 10:08.213
It was so nice
to see you again.

10:09.215 --> 10:12.803
- Hey, Dirk. How'd your math test go?
- What math test?

10:12.970 --> 10:15.473
- I thought you had a math test today.
- No.

10:15.556 --> 10:18.224
Did you turn in your paper
on the Berlin Airlift?

10:18.349 --> 10:19.935
Yeah, I got an extension.

10:20.351 --> 10:23.062
- Hey, George.
- So how'd it go with Mrs. Calloway?

10:23.187 --> 10:26.149
- We shook hands.
- Big deal.

10:26.316 --> 10:28.316
And I gave her
my phone number.

10:28.483 --> 10:30.778
Buchan said he'd have
already banged her by now.

10:30.904 --> 10:32.155
What?

10:32.279 --> 10:35.491
Just tell that deformed Scottish gorilla
to shut his fat face.

10:36.576 --> 10:38.785
That's my best friend's mother
he's talking about.

10:38.868 --> 10:42.539
I always thought that's why
you picked Dirk as your chapel partner.

10:43.038 --> 10:44.791
What are you, a lawyer?

10:44.916 --> 10:48.836
Hey, Mr. Blume.
Hey, it's Max Fischer.

10:48.920 --> 10:51.630
<i>- Oh, hi.
- Hey, Max, my mom just showed up.</i>

10:51.713 --> 10:53.551
<i>Is it okay if I leave early? Over.</i>

10:53.676 --> 10:55.427
Sure, Charlie.

11:01.223 --> 11:03.266
What's the secret, Max?

11:03.391 --> 11:05.017
- "The secret"?
- Yeah.

11:05.101 --> 11:08.523
Well, you seem to have it
pretty figured out.

11:08.606 --> 11:10.900
The secret.
I don't know. Uh...

11:10.942 --> 11:13.402
I think you just gotta find
something you love to do,

11:13.485 --> 11:17.072
and then do it
for the rest of your life.

11:17.239 --> 11:19.574
For me, it's going to Rushmore.

11:21.785 --> 11:22.494
Shotgun.

11:22.578 --> 11:26.125
- Hey, Ronny. Hey, Donny. How you guys...
- Get in the back. I said, "Shotgun".

11:26.208 --> 11:28.209
Get in the back, Donny.

11:30.377 --> 11:32.170
Let's go.

11:35.548 --> 11:37.049
Did you invite that kid
to your party?

11:37.133 --> 11:39.552
- Max Fischer? - Come on, Dad.
There's gonna be girls there.

11:39.635 --> 11:42.390
- I'd rather die.
- Pull your head out of your ass.

11:45.225 --> 11:46.977
- Good night, Mr. Littlejeans.
- Good night, Max.

11:47.060 --> 11:48.936
I'll see you tomorrow.

11:56.817 --> 11:58.904
May I see the back, please?

11:59.987 --> 12:01.909
Certainly.

12:04.828 --> 12:06.038
How's that?

12:06.121 --> 12:08.371
Thank you.

12:10.248 --> 12:13.251
I need a signature on this
geometry test, by the way.

12:13.335 --> 12:15.005
Let's see.

12:17.087 --> 12:19.257
- Hmm.
- I know, I know.

12:19.842 --> 12:21.259
A 37.

12:23.596 --> 12:26.140
Oh, I don't know
what to do anymore.

12:27.848 --> 12:30.266
It could have been worse.

12:30.434 --> 12:32.602
You almost got the "A".

12:32.685 --> 12:35.521
"Almost got the 'A"'?
Dad, what are you writing?

12:42.447 --> 12:45.116
Maybe I'm spending too much
of my time starting up clubs...

12:45.200 --> 12:47.368
and putting on plays.

12:47.868 --> 12:49.452
That's possible.

12:50.078 --> 12:53.456
I should probably be trying
harder to score chicks.

12:53.622 --> 12:56.503
That's the only thing
anybody really cares about.

12:57.002 --> 12:59.463
It's not my forte, unfortunately.

12:59.547 --> 13:01.673
It'll happen, Max. It's just...

13:01.756 --> 13:04.343
You're like one
of those clipper ship captains.

13:04.801 --> 13:06.679
You're married to the sea.

13:06.844 --> 13:08.722
Yes, that's true.

13:08.764 --> 13:12.225
But I've been out to sea
for a long time.

13:18.648 --> 13:21.484
- Hello.
- Hi.

13:30.659 --> 13:31.786
I like your hat.

13:32.704 --> 13:34.663
Oh, thank you.

13:35.205 --> 13:37.833
You're a teacher here,
aren't you?

13:39.918 --> 13:42.005
And this is your first year
at Rushmore, I take it.

13:42.171 --> 13:44.172
Uh-huh.

13:45.007 --> 13:47.966
And how long have you been a smoker,
if you don't mind me asking?

13:48.133 --> 13:51.764
Well, let's see now.
How old are you?

13:51.931 --> 13:53.183
Fifteen.

13:53.267 --> 13:56.476
- Since I was your age.
- You're kidding.

13:56.560 --> 13:58.145
You should quit.

13:58.270 --> 14:00.772
You're right.

14:01.273 --> 14:03.693
And I should mind my own business.

14:10.115 --> 14:12.492
Where did you go
to school, by the way?

14:12.618 --> 14:14.787
- Harvard.
- Really?

14:14.913 --> 14:16.288
That's a coincidence.

14:16.413 --> 14:20.041
My top schools where I want
to apply to are Oxford and the Sorbonne.

14:20.166 --> 14:22.460
My safety's Harvard.

14:22.668 --> 14:24.920
- That's very ambitious.
- Thank you.

14:25.045 --> 14:27.047
What do you want to study?

14:27.923 --> 14:30.801
Well... I haven't
decided for sure,

14:30.885 --> 14:35.640
but probably a double major
in mathematics and premed.

14:35.723 --> 14:37.640
What was your major?

14:37.723 --> 14:42.560
I didn't have a major, but my thesis
was on Latin American economic policy.

14:42.644 --> 14:46.984
Oh, that's interesting. Did you hear they're
not going to teach Latin here anymore?

14:47.151 --> 14:49.819
This was more like Central America.

14:49.903 --> 14:52.822
Oh, Central America
and whatnot. Hmm.

14:52.906 --> 14:55.659
But moving on:
They're gonna cancel Latin.

14:55.784 --> 14:58.827
They've got
to make room for Japanese.

14:58.911 --> 15:03.000
That's a shame because all the Romance
languages were based on Latin.

15:03.167 --> 15:05.085
Yeah, they are,
aren't they?

15:05.503 --> 15:08.088
Nihilo sanctum estne?

15:08.255 --> 15:11.840
What's that?
Oh, it's Latin, isn't it?

15:12.007 --> 15:13.842
What does that mean?

15:14.802 --> 15:16.970
"Is nothing sacred?"

15:23.685 --> 15:27.398
Sic transit gloria.
Glory fades.

15:27.523 --> 15:30.025
I'm Max Fischer.

15:30.192 --> 15:32.735
- Hi.
- Hi.

15:37.572 --> 15:40.327
- Come on, come on. File out.
- Sign here, please.

15:40.369 --> 15:42.162
- Sic transit gloria.
- All right, all right.

15:50.210 --> 15:52.339
In summation,
I have only one question:

15:53.172 --> 15:55.049
Is Latin dead?

16:00.347 --> 16:04.017
Why don't you just piss off,
Fischer, you dotty skid mark?

16:04.142 --> 16:05.476
Was that Latin?

16:12.899 --> 16:15.195
Never in my wildest
imagination...

16:15.278 --> 16:18.613
did I ever dream
I would have sons like these.

16:20.407 --> 16:22.993
What's your dad do, Max?

16:23.827 --> 16:28.538
He's a neurosurgeon...
at, uh, St. Joseph's Hospital.

16:28.705 --> 16:31.582
Personally, I could never see myself
cutting open somebody's brain,

16:31.665 --> 16:34.504
but he seems to enjoy it.

16:35.757 --> 16:37.632
Oh, no, no, no. I got this one.

16:40.091 --> 16:42.969
- So you were in Vietnam,
if I'm not mistaken? - Yeah.

16:45.055 --> 16:47.141
Were you in the shit?

16:47.225 --> 16:49.601
Yeah, I was in the shit.

16:51.103 --> 16:52.397
See you Sunday, Mr. Blume.

16:52.481 --> 16:55.317
- All right.
- What's on Sunday?

16:55.525 --> 16:57.985
Oh, that's right.
The twins' birthday party.

16:59.528 --> 17:01.362
Do you want to come?

17:01.487 --> 17:05.325
I'd love to, except I've already got
a previous obligation to attend to.

17:05.407 --> 17:08.704
Yeah. Thanks for
the invitation, though.

17:10.579 --> 17:13.084
Come work for me.

17:13.251 --> 17:18.253
- What do you mean?
- I mean, I could use someone like you.

17:19.673 --> 17:22.090
Look, I may not be rich, Mr. Blume.

17:22.174 --> 17:25.051
My father may only be
a doctor, but we manage.

17:25.176 --> 17:28.765
- One-twelves!
- Excuse me, Mr. Blume. Nice talking to you.

17:31.059 --> 17:32.769
You're on the team?

17:33.644 --> 17:34.770
I'm an alternate.

17:35.981 --> 17:38.816
How you doin'?
Good to see you again.

