a very convincing argument.

19:27.088 --> 19:31.883
I just thought you'd be pleased to hear
they're gonna continue the Latin program.

19:32.050 --> 19:33.928
I'm very impressed.

19:34.095 --> 19:36.681
Well, thank you very much.

19:37.265 --> 19:39.349
Hey, you need an assistant?

19:39.599 --> 19:41.351
- Do we get to have an
assistant around here?

19:41.352 --> 19:43.103
No, I doubt it.

19:43.144 --> 19:45.605
I'm on scholarship, though...
academic scholarship...

19:45.689 --> 19:48.274
so I get to do odd jobs and...

19:48.357 --> 19:50.943
Say, how did you decide
to teach at Rushmore?

19:51.026 --> 19:52.946
My husband went here.

19:55.364 --> 19:59.870
I, uh... I didn't know
you were married.

20:00.036 --> 20:01.955
Well, he's dead now.

20:02.038 --> 20:03.956
So I'm not, actually.

20:04.039 --> 20:06.291
When did he die?

20:06.457 --> 20:08.126
Last year.

20:09.710 --> 20:11.631
My mother's dead.

20:12.717 --> 20:14.759
I'm sorry to hear that.

20:14.926 --> 20:17.552
She died when I was seven.

20:17.719 --> 20:20.806
I guess we both have
dead people in our families.

20:25.394 --> 20:27.811
What's going on in here?

20:29.900 --> 20:32.194
These were just born.

20:34.404 --> 20:37.447
I don't want alloys. I want steel.

20:38.488 --> 20:41.825
I don't give a rat's ass what he says.

20:43.910 --> 20:45.954
Steel, Harry.

20:46.664 --> 20:49.832
- So you've changed your mind,
and you want the job? - No.

20:49.916 --> 20:52.169
But I've got an idea,
and I need some money.

20:52.878 --> 20:54.838
What Rushmore
needs is an aquarium...

20:54.922 --> 20:57.507
a first-class aquarium...
where the scientists can lecture...

20:57.590 --> 21:00.842
and the students can observe
the marine life in its natural habitat.

21:00.967 --> 21:03.470
- I don't know. What do you think, Ernie?
- An aquarium?

21:03.553 --> 21:05.536
What kind of fish?

21:05.537 --> 21:07.519
- Barracudas, stingrays,
electric eel, trout,

21:07.602 --> 21:10.521
hammerheads, piranhas,
giant squid, octopi...

21:10.604 --> 21:12.606
Piranhas? Really?

21:12.607 --> 21:14.607
- Yes, I'm talking to
a guy in South America.

21:14.690 --> 21:18.403
- What'd Guggenheim say?
- Nothing. I felt I should go to you first.

21:18.529 --> 21:20.404
Why?

21:20.571 --> 21:24.160
Because at this moment, I feel the
best strategy is to keep it low profile.

21:24.202 --> 21:27.163
The more preparation work I can do,
the stronger our case will be...

21:27.204 --> 21:30.206
- when we take it to the administration.
- How much money do you want?

21:30.706 --> 21:34.502
Thirty-five thousand dollars,
for the initial plans.

21:44.219 --> 21:46.389
I'll give you 2,500.

21:46.556 --> 21:47.932
Okay.

21:57.106 --> 21:59.820
<i># Trees #</i>

21:59.902 --> 22:03.865
<i># Swaying in the summer breeze #</i>

22:03.948 --> 22:07.159
<i># Showing off their silver leaves #</i>

22:07.243 --> 22:09.494
<i># As we walked by #</i>

22:09.578 --> 22:11.495
<i># Soft #</i>

22:11.662 --> 22:15.250
<i># Kisses on a summer's day #</i>

22:15.500 --> 22:18.671
<i># Laughing all our cares away #</i>

22:18.838 --> 22:21.673
<i># Just you and I #</i>

22:23.968 --> 22:26.928
<i># Sweet #</i>

22:27.052 --> 22:30.805
<i># Sleepy warmth of summer nights #</i>

22:30.972 --> 22:34.101
<i># Gazing at the distant lights #</i>

22:34.143 --> 22:36.104
<i># In the starry sky ##</i>

22:36.146 --> 22:38.104
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

23:16.017 --> 23:18.311
- Max.
- Mm-hmm?

23:18.478 --> 23:21.854
- Can I ask you something?
- Sure.

23:22.898 --> 23:26.693
Has it ever crossed your mind
that you're far too young for me?

23:31.782 --> 23:35.410
It crossed my mind that you might
consider that a possibility. Yeah.

23:35.494 --> 23:37.870
Quite apart from the fact
that you're a student...

23:37.995 --> 23:40.915
I'm not trying to pressure you
into anything, Miss Cross.

23:40.998 --> 23:42.937
- I'm surprised you
brought it up so bluntly.

23:42.938 --> 23:44.877
I just want to make sure...

23:47.674 --> 23:50.468
- We've become friends, haven't we?
- Yes.

23:50.593 --> 23:52.261
Good.

23:52.761 --> 23:55.054
And, um...

23:55.179 --> 23:58.683
the... the truth is, neither
one of us has the slightest idea...

23:58.766 --> 24:00.600
where this relationship is going.

24:00.725 --> 24:04.313
- We can't predict the future.
- We don't have a relationship, Max.

24:04.397 --> 24:07.235
- But we're friends.
- Yes, and that's all we're going to be.

24:07.360 --> 24:09.903
That's all I meant by "relationship".

24:10.028 --> 24:11.780
You want me to grab a dictionary?

24:11.905 --> 24:15.616
No, I just want to make sure
that we understand each other.

24:15.740 --> 24:17.701
I understand.

24:17.868 --> 24:20.871
You're not attracted to me.

24:21.037 --> 24:22.956
<i>C'est la vie.</i>

24:23.709 --> 24:26.169
Max, you're 15 years old.

24:26.835 --> 24:29.462
Attraction doesn't enter into it.

24:29.588 --> 24:31.507
If you say so.

24:31.632 --> 24:33.843
Look, all I'm getting at is that...

24:36.803 --> 24:39.346
that I've never met anyone like you.

24:41.139 --> 24:43.728
So you can take that
for whatever it's worth.

24:46.147 --> 24:50.567
I think I can safely say
I've never met anyone like you either.

24:54.445 --> 24:56.281
You haven't, have you?

24:59.115 --> 25:01.286
Want to shake hands?

25:02.411 --> 25:05.247
I'm glad we had this conversation.

25:05.414 --> 25:06.750
So am I.

25:08.458 --> 25:10.584
I can't wear a wire.
They're feeling me up every day.

25:10.709 --> 25:13.545
Oh, come on, Frank.
You'll have complete protection.

25:13.670 --> 25:15.507
Yeah, I've heard that one before.

25:15.589 --> 25:17.674
- I gotta put a dime in the meter.
- Sit down, Frank.

25:17.758 --> 25:21.094
Joe, go put a dime in the meter
for Officer Serpico.

25:21.261 --> 25:24.557
- Look, Serpico, if you agree
to testify in open court... - No!

25:24.682 --> 25:27.894
- No, what?
- No, I'm not gonna testify.

25:28.019 --> 25:29.436
Go, go, go.

25:29.937 --> 25:33.357
I'll expect your gun
and your badge on my desk...

25:34.274 --> 25:36.404
- Promise me one thing, O'Reilly.
- Name it.

25:36.446 --> 25:39.156
That you're gonna follow this thing
all the way to the end...

25:39.281 --> 25:41.533
of the line... where I got to be.

25:41.658 --> 25:43.325
So help me God.

25:43.492 --> 25:45.452
<i>- Someone coming out of the building.
- I've got something!</i>

25:45.536 --> 25:48.579
<i>- Wait. This could be it.
- There's action across the street.</i>

25:48.704 --> 25:50.999
<i>- Yeah, it's him.
- It's Snowman.</i>

25:53.252 --> 25:55.548
- He's getting on the "L" train!
- Take him!

25:57.882 --> 26:00.050
- What happened to the cannoli line?
- Max...

26:00.133 --> 26:03.345
You're supposed to say, "Forget about it,
Sanchez. The old man likes his cannolis".

26:03.428 --> 26:06.056
Look, I made a mistake, all right?
It didn't make any difference anyway.

26:06.181 --> 26:08.724
Hey, I'm letting it go,
but don't say it doesn't matter.

26:08.808 --> 26:11.394
- Every line matters.
- Get off my back!

26:11.477 --> 26:13.438
Don't fuck with my play!

26:14.106 --> 26:16.065
- You fucking cocksucker...
- Hey, break it up. Break it up.

26:16.232 --> 26:17.943
I'm gonna kill you.

26:24.949 --> 26:27.492
Max. Max.

26:52.436 --> 26:53.791
- I thought the acting
tonight was excellent.

26:53.792 --> 26:55.147
Thanks.

26:55.272 --> 26:57.856
Well, it was better in rehearsals.

26:58.023 --> 27:00.650
I'll catch up with you later, Dad.
I got a dinner to go to.

27:00.775 --> 27:04.069
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah. Cast and crew only.

27:04.153 --> 27:07.199
- Oh. You need some money?
- No, Dad.

27:10.325 --> 27:13.120
- Well, how was the slap?
- It was good.

27:13.245 --> 27:16.457
- There he is. Max, that was great.
- I'm so glad you could come.

27:16.583 --> 27:19.542
I want you to meet a friend of mine.
Peter Flynn, Max Fischer.

27:19.584 --> 27:22.003
- Hi.
- Who's this guy?

27:23.754 --> 27:26.195
Peter.

27:26.196 --> 27:28.637
- I really liked your
play. It was really cool.

27:28.802 --> 27:32.180
- Yeah.
- What happened to your nose?

27:33.098 --> 27:35.684
- I got punched in the face.
- Oh, boy.

27:35.768 --> 27:39.104
- What's your excuse?
- Hey, author.

27:39.230 --> 27:40.730
- How you doing?
- Nice job.

27:40.855 --> 27:43.359
- Thank you.
- Gonna get to meet your dad tonight?

27:43.442 --> 27:45.402
Oh, no. The old man's on call.

27:45.444 --> 27:47.405
Mr. Blume, I'd like you
to meet Miss Cross...

27:47.447 --> 27:50.407
and I didn't catch
this young gentleman's name.

27:51.741 --> 27:54.619
I like your nurse's uniform, guy.

27:54.744 --> 27:57.204
These are O.R. scrubs.

27:57.413 --> 27:59.497
"O.R." they?

28:01.417 --> 28:04.169
Well, they're totally
inappropriate for the occasion.

28:04.294 --> 28:06.549
Well, I didn't know
we were going to dinner.

28:06.715 --> 28:08.967
That's because you weren't invited.

28:09.133 --> 28:11.344
Take it easy, Max.

28:11.345 --> 28:13.554
- You were the one that
ordered him a whiskey and soda.

28:13.720 --> 28:15.429
So what's wrong with that?

28:15.555 --> 28:19.812
I can write a hit play. Why can't I have
a little drink to unwind myself?

28:21.688 --> 28:24.315
So, tell me, curly,
how do you know Miss Cross?

28:24.440 --> 28:26.483
- We went to Harvard together.
- Oh, that's great.

28:26.608 --> 28:28.526
I wrote a hit play
and directed it.

28:28.609 --> 28:30.946
So I'm not sweating it either.

28:31.113 --> 28:32.530
Can we get a check, please?

28:32.615 --> 28:34.825
- What do you think you're doing?
- Getting the check.

28:34.950 --> 28:36.868
No, you're not. Excuse me.

28:37.034 --> 28:38.997
I just want to thank you
for accommodating us.

28:39.122 --> 28:41.166
You see, we only thought
we were going to be three,

28:41.291 --> 28:44.669
but, uh, someone invited
himself along, so I apologize.

28:44.794 --> 28:48.170
- Quite all right, sir. Very well.
- Okay.

28:48.336 --> 28:50.006
You're being rude, Max.

28:50.173 --> 28:51.548
- No, I'm not.
- Yes, you are.

28:51.674 --> 28:55.052
No, I'm not. I'm just trying to figure out
why you brought this gentleman to my play...

28:55.178 --> 28:58.097
and my dinner,
which was invitation only.

28:58.680 --> 29:00.141
- Would you like me to
pass you the creamer, Doc?

29:00.142 --> 29:01.601
Yes, please.

29:02.686 --> 29:05.689
- What is wrong with you?
- What is wrong with you?

29:05.814 --> 29:09.647
You hurt my feelings!
This night was important to me!

29:09.814 --> 29:11.775
How did I hurt your feelings?

29:11.859 --> 29:16.241
Oh, my God!
I wrote a hit play!

29:20.409 --> 29:22.829
And I'm in love with you.

29:31.505 --> 29:33.508
Put that a little bit there.

29:52.899 --> 29:56.612
- Hi.
- Were you hiding over there?

29:56.779 --> 29:59.865
Uh, I didn't want
to disrupt class.

30:01.407 --> 30:03.368
What's that you're painting?

30:03.409 --> 30:06.662
That's a... a jellyfish.

30:07.120 --> 30:09.625
What can I do for you, Mr. Blume?

30:09.792 --> 30:11.836
Max wants to talk to you.

30:11.919 --> 30:15.672
- What for?
- To apologize, I think.

30:16.423 --> 30:18.173
Should we talk over here?

30:20.467 --> 30:21.720
He sent you?

30:21.762 --> 30:23.388
Yeah.

30:23.930 --> 30:26.308
Are you his messenger?

30:27.060 --> 30:29.645
No, I'm his friend.

30:29.895 --> 30:34.357
You were right.
I should not have allowed him to drink.

30:36.109 --> 30:39.694
I don't think
I should see Max anymore.

30:39.861 --> 30:42.405
Well, he's not gonna like
the sound of that.

30:42.572 --> 30:45.201
No. No, I know, but...

30:45.368 --> 30:48.202
I think I let him
get too attached.

30:49.122 --> 30:50.539
What do you think?

30:51.916 --> 30:53.876
Well, I think
you did your best.

30:57.880 --> 31:00.047
Tell him I'm sorry.

31:05.472 --> 31:07.432
Okay.

31:09.849 --> 31:12.185
What is your first name?

31:13.353 --> 31:16.982
Rosemary. What's yours?

31:17.148 --> 31:18.523
Herman.

31:22.945 --> 31:24.823
He wrote you a letter.

31:24.990 --> 31:26.700
<i>Dear Miss Cross,</i>

31:26.783 --> 31:29.201
<i>I would like to take this opportunity
to formally apologize...</i>

31:29.284 --> 31:31.827
<i>for the events
of the night of the 23rd.</i>

31:31.952 --> 31:34.538
<i>I'm not accustomed
to drinking alcohol.</i>

31:34.622 --> 31:38.835
<i>Please do me the service of coming to the
unveiling of a new venture I've undertaken.</i>

31:38.919 --> 31:41.795
<i>I hope you will attend,
if possible.</i>

31:41.962 --> 31:45.258
<i>I remain your friend, Max Fischer.</i>

31:52.555 --> 31:54.725
Cut the music and no more pictures.

31:54.808 --> 31:57.022
- What time is it, Alan?
- 1:15.

31:57.147 --> 32:00.149
Excuse me, gentlemen.
Hey, lay off the chips, Buchan.

32:00.899 --> 32:01.733
Did you see her?

32:01.817 --> 32:03.868
- She's not here.
- Well, go check her classroom.

32:03.951 --> 32:05.861
- Shall I go ahead and
take care of this tree?

32:05.962 --> 32:07.170
Let's wait a few minutes.

32:07.354 --> 32:09.531
- What's going on here, Maxie?
- Oh, hey, Coach Beck. Good to see you.

32:09.656 --> 32:11.243
This is where we're
putting in the new aquarium.

32:11.326 --> 32:13.244
I'm in charge of the committee,
if you can believe it.

32:13.327 --> 32:15.998
This is my baseball diamond.

32:16.207 --> 32:20.084
Yeah, I know, and I believe
it's being relocated a few feet over.

32:20.167 --> 32:22.878
Is it true the aquarium
will have piranhas?

32:23.045 --> 32:24.900
Where did you hear that?

32:24.901 --> 32:26.757
- My source indicated
that it was a possibility.

32:26.966 --> 32:29.342
Yes, it's true, but piranhas
are a very tricky species.

32:29.425 --> 32:32.178
- Max?
- Excuse me, George.

32:32.262 --> 32:34.181
- Bad news.
- What's the story?

32:34.265 --> 32:36.516
- She had a substitute teacher today.
- Why?

32:36.599 --> 32:38.309
I guess she got sick.

32:38.310 --> 32:40.020
- You know she's not
sick. Give me the phone.

32:44.107 --> 32:46.359
Janet, Max Fischer.
Is Mr. Blume there?

32:48.152 --> 32:49.777
Well, where is he?

32:50.403 --> 32:52.324
Goddamn it.
He's supposed to be here.

32:53.159 --> 32:54.994
I don't give a shit
about the barracudas,

32:55.035 --> 32:57.538
but, fuck it, I'm building it anyway.

32:59.414 --> 33:00.539
Max!

33:00.706 --> 33:02.542
Where are those damn
chain saws coming from?

33:02.625 --> 33:04.545
- He's right over there!
- Max!

33:04.628 --> 33:06.713
- Max!
- Oh, hello, Dr. Guggenheim.

33:06.796 --> 33:09.382
- What the hell do you think you're doing?
- We're having a fund-raiser for the...

33:09.465 --> 33:11.467
Turn that damn thing off!

33:12.218 --> 33:14.012
Tell me this isn't happening.

33:14.053 --> 33:17.140
Dr. Guggenheim, I'd rather not have
this conversation in front of my crew.

33:41.702 --> 33:43.371
...chapter seven.

33:44.288 --> 33:47.921
One more thing.
We have a new student with us today.

33:48.087 --> 33:51.422
His name's Max Fischer,
and he's actually asked...

33:51.547 --> 33:53.799
to say a few words to the class.

33:54.050 --> 33:56.719
Max, you want to take it away?

33:57.094 --> 33:59.514
Sure. Thanks very much.

34:01.139 --> 34:03.224
I just wanted to introduce myself.

34:09.063 --> 34:10.733
I'm Max Fischer.

34:10.775 --> 34:13.568
I'm a former student
of Rushmore Academy,

34:13.610 --> 34:16.321
which I recently
got expelled from.

34:18.531 --> 34:21.033
This is my first time
in a public school.

34:21.199 --> 34:24.496
I know you probably think I was born
with a silver spoon in my mouth,

34:24.578 --> 34:26.706
but I'm no elitist.

34:26.873 --> 34:29.167
I think you've got
some great facilities,

34:29.251 --> 34:32.753
and I'm really looking forward to making
the best of it here at Grover Cleveland.

34:33.254 --> 34:35.172
One footnote.

34:35.255 --> 34:37.716
I notice you don't have
a fencing team.

34:37.882 --> 34:41.054
Well, I'm gonna try my hardest
to start one up for you guys.

34:45.976 --> 34:48.186
- Max?
- Yes?

34:48.268 --> 34:51.272
Hi, I'm Margaret Yang.
I'm in Mrs. Whitney's class.

34:51.438 --> 34:54.567
- I just wanted to tell you that
I liked your speech. - Thank you.

34:54.692 --> 34:58.697
I don't think I've ever heard of anyone
asking to give a speech in class before.

34:58.780 --> 35:00.865
No? How unfortunate.

35:00.948 --> 35:04.202
The silver spoon remark
might rub some people the wrong way,

35:04.327 --> 35:06.120
- but I think I know...
- What do you mean?

35:06.245 --> 35:07.705
- Well...
- You know what?

35:07.788 --> 35:11.206
I gotta go into class in here.
I'll see you later, Mrs. Chang.

35:14.543 --> 35:16.630
En garde!

35:26.348 --> 35:28.431
Janet, Max Fischer. Is he in?

35:33.185 --> 35:34.315
Yeah?

35:35.024 --> 35:36.483
Okay.

35:37.568 --> 35:38.692
Hey, Max, how's it going?

35:38.817 --> 35:41.444
Terrible. Tell me something. When you
talked to Miss Cross the other day...

35:41.527 --> 35:43.905
Do you have a telephone pass?

35:44.071 --> 35:47.074
- Excuse me. Do you have a telephone pass?
- One second.

35:47.200 --> 35:49.181
I gotta tell ya, I don't know
what you see in her.

35:49.182 --> 35:51.162
I don'tthink she's right for you.

35:51.245 --> 35:52.831
What's that supposed to mean?

35:55.375 --> 35:57.669
I mean, she's not
that beautiful.

35:57.753 --> 36:01.088
She's not that intriguing.

36:01.172 --> 36:05.009
I mean, she has something that
you can't put your finger on, but...

36:05.133 --> 36:07.720
Look, Mr. Blume, your comments are
valuable, but let's get to the point.

36:07.844 --> 36:10.681
- Son?
- Will she see me again, yes or no?

36:11.098 --> 36:13.475
- No.
- Hang on.

36:13.600 --> 36:16.479
I'm talking on the telephone.

36:17.230 --> 36:19.064
Oh, come on.

36:19.356 --> 36:20.817
That's rude.

36:36.749 --> 36:38.250
Hey, Fischer.

36:39.543 --> 36:41.585
You better beat it, sonny.

36:41.794 --> 36:44.673
You know, Fischer,
I've been watching you.

36:45.590 --> 36:48.011
Showboat. Always talkin'.

36:48.137 --> 36:52.430
Picking a kid like Dirk because his mother's
a great piece, and then getting nowhere.

36:52.556 --> 36:54.516
Like everything you do.

36:54.599 --> 36:57.643
Big show. No results.

36:57.852 --> 37:02.313
What do you call getting a hand job from
Mrs. Calloway in the back of her Jaguar?

37:03.064 --> 37:04.694
A fucking lie.

37:04.861 --> 37:09.531
You think I got kicked out
for just the aquarium? Nah.

37:09.656 --> 37:13.284
It was the hand job.
You want to know something else?

37:13.450 --> 37:15.120
It was worth it.

37:17.538 --> 37:20.331
I'm sorry I embarrassed you at dinner.

37:20.456 --> 37:23.754
And please apologize
to what's-his-name for me.

37:24.212 --> 37:28.049
I will. You okay?

37:28.216 --> 37:31.969
Yeah, I'm fine,
but I miss Rushmore.

37:32.135 --> 37:34.095
I miss the seasons.

37:34.637 --> 37:37.099
Watching the leaves change.

37:37.266 --> 37:40.308
By the way, what time
does the library close?

37:40.475 --> 37:43.104
I've got an overdue book
to turn in.

37:50.110 --> 37:52.153
That is your handwriting,
isn't it?

37:53.697 --> 37:54.947
My husband gave me this book...

37:55.031 --> 37:58.493
when he came to visit England
when I was 13 and he went to Rushmore.

37:58.576 --> 38:01.163
So when he died,
I gave it to the library here.

38:03.958 --> 38:06.461
You remind me of him, you know?

38:07.378 --> 38:08.962
I do?

38:09.463 --> 38:11.130
How?

38:11.214 --> 38:13.215
Well...

38:14.342 --> 38:18.182
you were a member of
the Rushmore Beekeepers, weren't you?

38:18.306 --> 38:20.934
Yeah. I was president of them.

38:21.141 --> 38:22.935
He founded that club.

38:30.609 --> 38:33.236
Do you think we can be
friends again, Miss Cross?

38:34.111 --> 38:38.033
- In-In a strictly platonic way?
- Of course I do.

38:38.158 --> 38:42.120
Do you think you can make a go of it
and settle down at Grover Cleveland?

38:42.954 --> 38:45.997
Yeah, but I need a tutor.

38:46.540 --> 38:52.086
<i># In the midnight moonlight
I'll #</i>

38:52.629 --> 38:56.800
<i># Be walking
a long and lonely mile #</i>

38:58.095 --> 39:02.139
<i># And every time I do #</i>

39:03.599 --> 39:08.394
<i># I keep seeing
this picture of you #</i>

39:08.560 --> 39:11.020
<i># Here comes my baby #</i>

39:11.229 --> 39:13.651
<i># Here she comes now #</i>

39:14.111 --> 39:17.238
